  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA316-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu piriviṭai melinta talaimakaḷait tōḻi vaṟpuṟuttatu (ET: vaṟpuṟuttiyatu).</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante encouraged HER who had become weak in the time of separation.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA316">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            maṭava tamma maṇiniṟa veḻili</l>
<l>            malariṉ mauva ṉalamvarak kāṭṭik</l>
<l>            kayalē ruṇkaṭ kaṉaṅkuḻai yivaini</l>
<l>            ṉeyiṟēr poḻuti ṉēytaru vēmeṉak</l>
<l>            kaṇṇakaṉ vicumpiṉ matiyeṉa vuṇarntaniṉ</l>
<l>            ṉaṉṉuta ṉīvic ceṉṟōr tannacai</l>
<l>            vāyttuvaral vārā vaḷavai yattak</l>
<l>            kaṉmicai yaṭukkam putaiyak kālvīḻttut</l>
<l>            taḷitaru taṇkār talaii</l>
<l>            viḷiyicait taṉṟāl viyaliṭat tāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Foolish, alas, [is] the sapphire-coloured cloud:</l>
<l>It has really sounded loudly in the wide area,</l>
<l rend="indent">offering dripping cool rain,</l>
<l rend="indent">letting the wind fall in, while the mountain side is buried on stony</l>
<l rend="indent">elevation,</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the road, before<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">vāyttu varal vārā aḷavai</term>: literally here the construction is impersonal ("to the extent that HIS reaching [and] coming does not come...").</note> he reaches [and] comes [back]</l>
<l rend="indent4">to [the place of] his yearning,</l>
<l rend="indent">he who has gone stroking your good forehead,</l>
<l rend="indent2">perceiving it as moon in the eye-widening<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kaṇ akaṉ</term>: this epithet can either refer to the width of the sky (as K.P. and T.V.G. take it), though then we would rather expect <term xml:lang="ta">akaṉ kaṇ</term>, or to the admiration of the observer.</note> sky,</l>
<l rend="indent2">saying</l>
<l rend="indent3">“we will be back at the time these resemble your teeth,</l>
<l rend="indent3">[o you of] thick earrings [and] carp-like collyrium eyes,”</l>
<l rend="indent2">pointing at the blossomless wild jasmine, to attain beauty<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">nalam</term> here doubtless refers to the flowering state of the jasmine, but it is less easy to make sense of an infinitive. A verbal noun might be about apt: pointing at a process.</note>.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
